  <source>Poitiers University Hospital</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Steinert's disease is an orphan disease. The prognosis of patients with this disease is
      conditioned by cardiac involvement. Search an early stage alterations in contractile function
      in subjects suffering from dystrophy would detect patients at risk of sudden death. The first
      stage of work is to validate the tools to detect early stage of infringement systolic
      function in a population of patients with myotonic dystrophy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
